  "description": "Achille Mbembe (1957–) is a Cameroonian post-colonial theorist whose work extends Foucauldian biopolitics into necropolitics — the analysis of contemporary regimes of power as the production and management of death-worlds — and develops a comprehensive critique of the colonial constitution of modern subjectivity.",
